{
  "Multiplication": {
    "title": "What is Multiplication?",
    "content": "<p class=\"mb-4\">Think of multiplication as a super-fast way of adding! It's for when you have groups of the same number.</p><p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Example: The Cookie Plate</strong></p><p class=\"mb-2\">Imagine you have 4 plates, and each plate has 3 cookies.</p><div class=\"text-2xl mb-2\">ğŸªğŸªğŸª &nbsp; ğŸªğŸªğŸª &nbsp; ğŸªğŸªğŸª &nbsp; ğŸªğŸªğŸª</div><p class=\"mb-2\">You could add them up: <code class=\"bg-gray-200 p-1 rounded\">3 + 3 + 3 + 3 = 12</code></p><p class=\"mb-4\">But the faster way is to multiply! We say we have \"4 groups of 3\".</p><p class=\"mb-2\">We write this as: <code class=\"bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 font-bold p-1 rounded\">4 x 3 = 12</code></p><p>The 'x' symbol means \"times\" or \"groups of\". So, 4 times 3 is 12. It's the same answer, just much quicker!</p>"
  },
  "Division": {
    "title": "What is Division?",
    "content": "<p class=\"mb-4\">Division is all about sharing equally or splitting something into equal groups.</p><p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Example: Sharing Stickers</strong></p><p class=\"mb-2\">Let's say you have 12 stickers and you want to share them equally among 3 friends.</p><div class=\"text-2xl mb-2\">â­ â­ â­ â­ â­ â­ â­ â­ â­ â­ â­ â­</div><p class=\"mb-2\">How many stickers does each friend get? You are dividing 12 into 3 groups.</p><div class=\"text-2xl mb-2\">(â­ â­ â­ â­) &nbsp; (â­ â­ â­ â­) &nbsp; (â­ â­ â­ â­) </div><p class=\"mb-4\">We write this as: <code class=\"bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 font-bold p-1 rounded\">12 Ã· 3 = 4</code></p><p class=\"mb-2\">The 'Ã·' symbol means \"divide\". So, 12 divided by 3 is 4. Each friend gets 4 stickers!</p><p><strong>Hint:</strong> Division is the opposite of multiplication! If you know <code class=\"bg-gray-200 p-1 rounded\">3 x 4 = 12</code>, then you also know <code class=\"bg-gray-200 p-1 rounded\">12 Ã· 3 = 4</code>.</p>"
  },
  "Fractions": {
    "title": "What are Fractions?",
    "content": "<p class=\"mb-4\">A fraction is a part of a whole thing. Think of a pizza!</p><p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Example: The Pizza Slice</strong></p><p class=\"mb-2\">A whole pizza is one whole thing. If you cut it into 4 equal slices, each slice is a fraction of the whole pizza.</p><div class=\"flex justify-center my-4\"><svg width=\"100\" height=\"100\" viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\"><circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"45\" fill=\"#FBBF24\" stroke=\"#D97706\" stroke-width=\"2\"/><path d=\"M 50 50 L 50 5 A 45 45 0 0 1 95 50 Z\" fill=\"#FDE68A\" stroke=\"#D97706\" stroke-width=\"2\"/></svg></div><p class=\"mb-2\">A fraction has two parts:</p><ul><li class=\"mb-2\">The <strong>Numerator</strong> (top number) tells you how many slices you have. (e.g., 1)</li><li class=\"mb-2\">The <strong>Denominator</strong> (bottom number) tells you how many equal slices the whole pizza was cut into. (e.g., 4)</li></ul><p class=\"mt-4\">So, if you have 1 slice of a pizza cut into 4, you have <code class=\"bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 font-bold p-1 rounded\">1/4</code> of the pizza!</p>"
  },
  "Area": {
    "title": "What is Area?",
    "content": "<p class=\"mb-4\">Area is the amount of space inside a flat, 2D shape. It's like counting the squares on a chocolate bar!</p><p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Example: A Chocolate Bar</strong></p><p class=\"mb-2\">Imagine a chocolate bar that is 4 squares long and 3 squares wide.</p><div class=\"flex justify-center my-4\"><svg baseProfile=\"full\" height=\"200px\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"300px\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" xmlns:ev=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/xml-events\" xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\"><defs /><rect fill=\"#84563C\" height=\"160\" stroke=\"black\" width=\"120\" x=\"90.0\" y=\"20.0\" /><line stroke=\"black\" stroke-dasharray=\"2,2\" x1=\"130.0\" x2=\"130.0\" y1=\"20.0\" y2=\"180.0\" /><line stroke=\"black\" stroke-dasharray=\"2,2\" x1=\"170.0\" x2=\"170.0\" y1=\"20.0\" y2=\"180.0\" /><line stroke=\"black\" stroke-dasharray=\"2,2\" x1=\"90.0\" x2=\"210.0\" y1=\"60.0\" y2=\"60.0\" /><line stroke=\"black\" stroke-dasharray=\"2,2\" x1=\"90.0\" x2=\"210.0\" y1=\"100.0\" y2=\"100.0\" /><line stroke=\"black\" stroke-dasharray=\"2,2\" x1=\"90.0\" x2=\"210.0\" y1=\"140.0\" y2=\"140.0\" /><text fill=\"black\" font-size=\"12px\" text-anchor=\"middle\" x=\"150.0\" y=\"10.0\">3 units</text><text fill=\"black\" font-size=\"12px\" text-anchor=\"end\" transform=\"rotate(-90,80.0,100.0)\" x=\"80.0\" y=\"100.0\">4 units</text></svg></div><p class=\"mb-2\">To find the area, you can count all the squares (there are 12), or you can use multiplication!</p><p class=\"mb-4\">The formula is: <code class=\"bg-gray-200 p-1 rounded\">Area = Length x Width</code></p><p>So, for our chocolate bar: <code class=\"bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 font-bold p-1 rounded\">4 x 3 = 12</code> square units.</p>"
  },
  "Perimeter": {
    "title": "What is Perimeter?",
    "content": "<p class=\"mb-4\">Perimeter is the total distance all the way around the outside of a shape. It's like walking around a fence that encloses a park.</p><p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Example: A Rectangular Park</strong></p><p class=\"mb-2\">Imagine a park that is 5 meters long and 3 meters wide.</p><div class=\"my-4 flex justify-center\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\"> <!-- Rectangle --> <rect x=\"25\" y=\"30.0\" width=\"100\" height=\"60.0\" fill=\"lightblue\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"4\"/> <!-- Length label --> <text x=\"70.0\" y=\"20.0\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"black\">Length: 5m</text> <!-- Width label --> <text x=\"12\" y=\"30.0\" text-anchor=\"end\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"black\" transform=\"rotate(-90 12,30.0)\">Width: 3m</text> </svg></div><p class=\"mb-2\">To find the perimeter, you add up the lengths of all four sides:</p><p class=\"mb-4\"><code class=\"bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 font-bold p-1 rounded\">5 + 3 + 5 + 3 = 16</code> meters.</p><p>You have to walk 16 meters to go all the way around the park's fence!</p>"
  },
  "Volume": {
    "title": "What is Volume?",
    "content": "<p class=\"mb-4\">Volume is the amount of space a 3D object takes up. Think about how many Lego blocks it takes to build a box.</p><p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Example: Building with Blocks</strong></p><p class=\"mb-2\">Imagine you build a small box with Lego blocks. It's 3 blocks long, 2 blocks wide, and 2 blocks high.</p><div class=\"flex justify-center my-4\"><svg baseProfile=\"tiny\" height=\"200\" width=\"300\" version=\"1.2\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" xmlns:ev=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/xml-events\" xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\"><defs/><polygon points=\"106.7,55.0 124.0,65.0 106.7,75.0 89.4,65.0\" fill=\"#cccccc\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"89.4,65.0 106.7,75.0 106.7,95.0 89.4,85.0\" fill=\"#aaaaaa\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"106.7,75.0 124.0,65.0 124.0,85.0 106.7,95.0\" fill=\"#888888\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"124.0,65.0 141.3,75.0 124.0,85.0 106.7,75.0\" fill=\"#cccccc\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"106.7,75.0 124.0,85.0 124.0,105.0 106.7,95.0\" fill=\"#aaaaaa\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"124.0,85.0 141.3,75.0 141.3,95.0 124.0,105.0\" fill=\"#888888\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"141.3,75.0 158.7,85.0 141.3,95.0 124.0,85.0\" fill=\"#cccccc\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"124.0,85.0 141.3,95.0 141.3,115.0 124.0,105.0\" fill=\"#aaaaaa\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"141.3,95.0 158.7,85.0 158.7,105.0 141.3,115.0\" fill=\"#888888\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"89.4,65.0 106.7,75.0 89.4,85.0 72.1,75.0\" fill=\"#cccccc\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"72.1,75.0 89.4,85.0 89.4,105.0 72.1,95.0\" fill=\"#aaaaaa\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"89.4,85.0 106.7,75.0 106.7,95.0 89.4,105.0\" fill=\"#888888\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"106.7,75.0 124.0,85.0 106.7,95.0 89.4,85.0\" fill=\"#cccccc\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"89.4,85.0 106.7,95.0 106.7,115.0 89.4,105.0\" fill=\"#aaaaaa\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"106.7,95.0 124.0,85.0 124.0,105.0 106.7,115.0\" fill=\"#888888\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"124.0,85.0 141.3,95.0 124.0,105.0 106.7,95.0\" fill=\"#cccccc\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"106.7,95.0 124.0,105.0 124.0,125.0 106.7,115.0\" fill=\"#aaaaaa\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"124.0,105.0 141.3,95.0 141.3,115.0 124.0,125.0\" fill=\"#888888\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"106.7,35.0 124.0,45.0 106.7,55.0 89.4,45.0\" fill=\"#cccccc\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"89.4,45.0 106.7,55.0 106.7,75.0 89.4,65.0\" fill=\"#aaaaaa\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"106.7,55.0 124.0,45.0 124.0,65.0 106.7,75.0\" fill=\"#888888\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"124.0,45.0 141.3,55.0 124.0,65.0 106.7,55.0\" fill=\"#cccccc\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"106.7,55.0 124.0,65.0 124.0,85.0 106.7,75.0\" fill=\"#aaaaaa\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"124.0,65.0 141.3,55.0 141.3,75.0 124.0,85.0\" fill=\"#888888\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"141.3,55.0 158.7,65.0 141.3,75.0 124.0,65.0\" fill=\"#cccccc\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"124.0,65.0 141.3,75.0 141.3,95.0 124.0,85.0\" fill=\"#aaaaaa\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"141.3,75.0 158.7,65.0 158.7,85.0 141.3,95.0\" fill=\"#888888\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"89.4,45.0 106.7,55.0 89.4,65.0 72.1,55.0\" fill=\"#cccccc\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"72.1,55.0 89.4,65.0 89.4,85.0 72.1,75.0\" fill=\"#aaaaaa\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"89.4,65.0 106.7,55.0 106.7,75.0 89.4,85.0\" fill=\"#888888\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"106.7,55.0 124.0,65.0 106.7,75.0 89.4,65.0\" fill=\"#cccccc\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"89.4,65.0 106.7,75.0 106.7,95.0 89.4,85.0\" fill=\"#aaaaaa\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"106.7,75.0 124.0,65.0 124.0,85.0 106.7,95.0\" fill=\"#888888\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"124.0,65.0 141.3,75.0 124.0,85.0 106.7,75.0\" fill=\"#cccccc\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"106.7,75.0 124.0,85.0 124.0,105.0 106.7,95.0\" fill=\"#aaaaaa\" stroke=\"black\"/><polygon points=\"124.0,85.0 141.3,75.0 141.3,95.0 124.0,105.0\" fill=\"#888888\" stroke=\"black\"/></svg></div><p class=\"mb-2\">To find the volume, you multiply all three measurements:</p><p class=\"mb-4\"><code class=\"bg-gray-200 p-1 rounded\">Volume = Length x Width x Height</code></p><p>So, for our box: <code class=\"bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 font-bold p-1 rounded\">3 x 2 x 2 = 12</code> blocks.</p><p>The volume of the box is 12 blocks!</p>"
